tms.name: TM00
tms.description: It looks just like a regular TM, but it doesn't do anything.

tms.name: TM01
tms.description: The user sharpens its claws to boost its Attack stat and accuracy.

tms.name: TM02
tms.description: The user slashes the target with huge, sharp claws.

tms.name: TM03
tms.description: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack the target. This attack does physical damage.

tms.name: TM04
tms.description: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to raise its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

tms.name: TM05
tms.description: The target is scared off and replaced by another Pokémon in its party. In the wild, the battle ends.

tms.name: TM06
tms.description: A move that leaves the target badly poisoned. Its poison damage worsens every turn.

tms.name: TM07
tms.description: Summons a hailstorm that lasts for five turns. The hailstorm damages all types except Ice.

tms.name: TM08
tms.description: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, boosting both its Attack and Defense stats.

tms.name: TM09
tms.description: The user drenches the target in a special poisonous liquid. Its power is doubled if the target is poisoned.

tms.name: TM10
tms.description: A unique attack that varies in type and intensity depending on the Pokémon using it.

tms.name: TM11
tms.description: The user intensifies the sun for five turns, powering up Fire-type moves.

tms.name: TM12
tms.description: The target is taunted into a rage that allows it to use only attack moves for three turns.

tms.name: TM13
tms.description: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy. It may also freeze the target solid.

tms.name: TM14
tms.description: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike the opposing team. It may also freeze them solid.

tms.name: TM15
tms.description: The target is attacked with a powerful beam. The user must rest on the next turn to regain its energy.

tms.name: TM16
tms.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to suppress damage from special attacks for five turns.

tms.name: TM17
tms.description: It enables the user to evade all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

tms.name: TM18
tms.description: The user summons a heavy rain that falls for five turns, powering up Water-type moves.

tms.name: TM19
tms.description: The user makes the target float with its psychic power. The target is easier to hit for three turns.

tms.name: TM20
tms.description: The user creates a protective field that prevents status problems for five turns.

tms.name: TM21
tms.description: A full-power attack that grows more powerful the less the user likes its Trainer.

tms.name: TM22
tms.description: A two-turn attack. The user gathers light, then blasts a bundled beam on the second turn.

tms.name: TM23
tms.description: The user throws a stone or similar projectile to attack a foe. A flying Pokémon will fall to the ground if hit.

tms.name: TM24
tms.description: A strong electric blast is loosed at the target. It may also leave the target with paralysis.

tms.name: TM25
tms.description: A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on the target to inflict damage. It may also leave the target with paralysis.

tms.name: TM26
tms.description: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.

tms.name: TM27
tms.description: A full-power attack that grows more powerful the more the user likes its Trainer.

tms.name: TM28
tms.description: The user burrows, then attacks on the second turn. It can also be used to exit dungeons.

tms.name: TM29
tms.description: The target is hit by a strong telekinetic force. It may also reduce the target's Sp. Def stat.

tms.name: TM30
tms.description: The user hurls a shadowy blob at the target. It may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tms.name: TM31
tms.description: The user attacks with tough fists, etc. It can also break any barrier such as Light Screen and Reflect.

tms.name: TM32
tms.description: By moving rapidly, the user makes illusory copies of itself to raise its evasiveness.

tms.name: TM33
tms.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to suppress damage from physical attacks for five turns.

tms.name: TM34
tms.description: It swamps the area around the user with a giant sludge wave. It may also poison those hit.

tms.name: TM35
tms.description: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. It may also leave the target with a burn.

tms.name: TM36
tms.description: Unsanitary sludge is hurled at the target. It may also poison the target.

tms.name: TM37
tms.description: A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to hurt all combatants except the Rock, Ground, and Steel types.

tms.name: TM38
tms.description: The foe is attacked with an intense blast of all-consuming fire. It may also leave the target with a burn.

tms.name: TM39
tms.description: Boulders are hurled at the target. It also lowers the target's Speed by preventing its movement.

tms.name: TM40
tms.description: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. The attack lands without fail.

tms.name: TM41
tms.description: The user torments and enrages the target, making it incapable of using the same move twice in a row.

tms.name: TM42
tms.description: An attack move that doubles its power if the user is poisoned, paralyzed, or has a burn.

tms.name: TM43
tms.description: The user cloaks itself with flame and attacks. Building up more power, it raises the user's Speed stat.

tms.name: TM44
tms.description: The user goes to sleep for two turns. It fully restores the user's HP and heals any status problem.

tms.name: TM45
tms.description: If it is the opposite gender of the user, the target becomes infatuated and less likely to attack.

tms.name: TM46
tms.description: The user attacks and steals the target's held item simultaneously. It can't steal if the user holds an item.

tms.name: TM47
tms.description: The user attacks the target's legs swiftly, reducing the target's Speed stat.

tms.name: TM48
tms.description: The user attacks the target with a song. Others can join in the Round to increase the power of the attack.

tms.name: TM49
tms.description: The user attacks the target with an echoing voice. If this move is used every turn, it does greater damage.

tms.name: TM50
tms.description: The user attacks the target at full power. The attack's recoil sharply reduces the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tms.name: TM51
tms.description: The user teleports using a strange power and switches its place with one of its allies.

tms.name: TM52
tms.description: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. It may also lower the target's Sp. Def.

tms.name: TM53
tms.description: The user draws power from nature and fires it at the target. It may also lower the target's Sp. Def.

tms.name: TM54
tms.description: A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is left with at least 1 HP.

tms.name: TM55
tms.description: The user attacks the target with a pulsing blast of water. It may also confuse the target.

tms.name: TM56
tms.description: The user flings its held item at the target as an attack. Its power and effects depend on the item.

tms.name: TM57
tms.description: The user fires a concentrated bundle of electricity. It may also raise the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tms.name: TM58
tms.description: The user hurls the foe into the sky, then drops it on the next turn. The foe cannot attack while in the sky.

tms.name: TM59
tms.description: The user attacks the target with fire. If the target is holding a Berry, the Berry becomes burnt up and unusable.

tms.name: TM60
tms.description: The user suppresses the target and makes its move go last.

tms.name: TM61
tms.description: The user shoots a sinister, bluish-white flame at the target to inflict a burn.

tms.name: TM62
tms.description: The user nimbly strikes the target. If the user is not holding an item, this attack inflicts massive damage.

tms.name: TM63
tms.description: It prevents the target from using its held item. Its Trainer is also prevented from using items on it.

tms.name: TM64
tms.description: The user explodes to inflict damage on those around it. The user faints upon using this move.

tms.name: TM65
tms.description: The user slashes with a sharp claw made from shadows. It has a high critical-hit ratio.

tms.name: TM66
tms.description: The user stores power, then attacks. If the user can use this attack after the foe, its power is doubled.

tms.name: TM67
tms.description: The user gets revenge for a fainted ally. If an ally fainted in the previous turn, this attack's damage increases.

tms.name: TM68
tms.description: The user charges at the target using every bit of its power. The user must rest on the next turn.

tms.name: TM69
tms.description: The user polishes its body to reduce drag. It sharply raises the Speed stat.

tms.name: TM70
tms.description: The user lands and rests its body. It restores the user's HP by up to half of its max HP.

tms.name: TM71
tms.description: The user stabs the foe with sharpened stones from below. It has a high critical-hit ratio.

tms.name: TM72
tms.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tms.name: TM73
tms.description: A weak electric charge is launched at the target. It causes paralysis if it hits.

tms.name: TM74
tms.description: The user tackles the target with a high-speed spin. The slower the user, the greater the damage.

tms.name: TM75
tms.description: A frenetic dance to uplift the fighting spirit. It sharply raises the user's Attack stat.

tms.name: TM76
tms.description: Resisting, the user attacks the opposing Pokémon. The targets' Sp. Atk stat is reduced.

tms.name: TM77
tms.description: The user hypnotizes itself into copying any stat change made by the target.

tms.name: TM78
tms.description: The user stomps down on the ground and attacks everything in the area. The targets' Speed stat is reduced.

tms.name: TM79
tms.description: The user blows a cold breath on the target. This attack always results in a critical hit.

tms.name: TM80
tms.description: Large boulders are hurled at the opposing team to inflict damage. They may also make the targets flinch.

tms.name: TM81
tms.description: The user slashes at the target by crossing its scythes or claws as if they were a pair of scissors.

tms.name: TM82
tms.description: The user knocks away the target and drags out another Pokémon in its party. In the wild, the battle ends.

tms.name: TM83
tms.description: The user is roused, and its Attack and Sp. Atk stats increase.

tms.name: TM84
tms.description: The target is stabbed with a tentacle or arm steeped in poison. It may also poison the target.

tms.name: TM85
tms.description: The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target. It absorbs half the damage caused to heal the user's HP.

tms.name: TM86
tms.description: The user snares the target with grass and trips it. The heavier the target, the greater the damage.

tms.name: TM87
tms.description: The user enrages and confuses the target. However, it also sharply raises the target's Attack stat.

tms.name: TM88
tms.description: While it is asleep, the user randomly uses one of the moves it knows.

tms.name: TM89
tms.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tms.name: TM90
tms.description: The user makes a copy of itself using some of its HP. The copy serves as the user's decoy.

tms.name: TM91
tms.description: The user gathers all its light energy and releases it at once. It may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tms.name: TM92
tms.description: The user creates a bizarre space in which slower Pokémon get to move first for five turns.

tms.name: TM93
tms.description: The user shrouds itself in electricity and smashes into its target. It also damages the user a little.

tms.name: TM94
tms.description: The user attacks with a punch that can shatter a rock. It may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tms.name: TM95
tms.description: The user yells as if it is ranting about something, making the target's Sp. Atk stat decrease.

tms.name: TM96
tms.description: Borrowing the power of the moon, the user attacks the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tms.name: TM97
tms.description: The user stimulates its brain by thinking bad thoughts. It sharply raises the user's Sp. Atk.

tms.name: TM98
tms.description: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting, passing along any stat changes.

tms.name: TM99
tms.description: The user performs a beautiful dance. It boosts the user's Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

tms.name: TM100
tms.description: A strong wind blows away the foe's obstacles such as Light Screen. It also lowers their evasion.

tms.name: TM101
tms.description: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that boosts its Attack and Speed stats.

tms.name: TM102
tms.description: The user scatters bursts of spores that induce sleep.

tms.name: TM103
tms.description: The user lays a trap of poison spikes at the foe's feet. They poison foes that switch into battle.

tms.name: TM104
tms.description: Restoring its own cells, the user restores its own HP by half of its max HP.

tms.name: TM105
tms.description: The user lunges at the target at a speed that makes it almost invisible. It is sure to strike first.

tms.name: TM106
tms.description: The user steals the target's HP with a kiss. The user's HP is restored by over half of the damage taken by the target.

tms.name: TM107
tms.description: The user plays rough with the target and attacks it.

tms.name: TM108
tms.description: A second-turn attack move where critical hits land more easily. It may also make the target flinch.

tms.name: TM109
tms.description: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

tms.name: TM110
tms.description: This move reduces damage from attacks for five turns. This can be used only in a hailstorm.

tms.name: TM111
tms.description: The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a powerful flash.

tms.name: TM112
tms.description: The user focuses its mind before launching a punch. It will fail if the user is hit before it is used.

tms.name: TM113
tms.description: The target is infested and unable to flee for four to five turns.

tms.name: TM114
tms.description: The user drains the target's blood. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

tms.name: TM115
tms.description: Striking opponents repeatedly makes the user's fists harder, raising the user's Attack stat.

tms.name: TM116
tms.description: The user strikes the target with a quick jolt of electricity. This attack cannot be evaded.

tms.name: TM117
tms.description: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

tms.name: TM118
tms.description: The target is hit with wings of steel. It may also raise the user's Defense stat.

tms.name: TM119
tms.description: The user attacks driven by frustration. Power increases if the user's previous move failed.

tms.name: TM120
tms.description: The user attacks the target's throat. The target cannot use sound-based moves for two turns.

tms.name: TM121
tms.description: The user shoots boiling hot water at its target. It may also leave the target with a burn.

hms.name: HM01
hms.description: The target is cut with a scythe or claw. It can also be used to cut down thin trees.

hms.name: HM02
hms.description: The user soars, then strikes on the second turn. It can also be used to fly to any familiar town.

hms.name: HM03
hms.description: It swamps the area around the user with a giant wave. It can also be used for crossing water.

hms.name: HM04
hms.description: The target is slugged with a punch thrown at maximum power. This move can also be used to move boulders.

hms.name: HM05
hms.description: The user charges the target at an awesome speed. It can also be used to climb a waterfall.

hms.name: HM06
hms.description: The user dives on the first turn, and floats up and attacks on the second. It can be used to dive in the ocean.

hms.name: HM07
hms.description: The user teleports out of sight. It can also be used to teleport to any familiar Pokémon Center

hms.name: HM08
hms.description: The user flashes a bright light that cuts the target's accuracy. It can also be used to illuminate caves.

hms.name: HM09
hms.description: The user bounces up high, then drops on the foe on the second turn. It can also be used for jumping over holes.

hms.name: HM10
hms.description: The user attacks the target by smashing into it with incredible force. It can also be used to climb up cliffs.
